Disney’s Lucasfilm is developing several Star Wars films which focus on particular characters, according to Hollywood Reporter. These include a film about Boba Fett, which the report stated will be written and directed by James Mangold. Mangold worked on X-Men films such as 2017’s Logan, which he wrote and directed. Before Logan, he directed The Wolverine in 2013. According to the report, Mangold is said to be collaborating with Simon Kinberg, the writer and producer behind the X-Men franchise. Kinberg is rumoured to be cowriting and producing the Boba Fett film. Other characters Lucasfilm is developing movies around include Obi-Wan Kenobi. The report stated that Stephen Daldry is in negotiations to direct the film, but no writers are working on a script as yet.